outputs.description: Support strengthening of PTAs in targeted communities and the role of fathers and community members in early reading
Key partners/stakeholders are mobilized to support and engage in the promotion and protection of children's rights by 2016.
By December 2016, most at risk young people are enabled to reduce their vulnerability through utilization of health, secondchance education and protective services.

By 2016, data collection and management systems provide sex and age disaggregated data on women and children for national planningand timely reporting on MDGs, CRC and Vision 2030 at national and sub-national levels.
Governance structures and systems that are necessary to adequately manage risks and achieve programme results.
Improved planning, coordination, collaboration mechanisms and networking arrangements in place to strengthen the Child Protectionsystem.
Effective and efficient management of human capacity
Effective and efficient management and stewardship of financial resources.
By 2016, stronger national systems to identify children with disabilities and increased support for children with disabilities intargeted communities.
By 2016, all 6-12 year old girls and boys in the targeted communities attend schools that meet CFS standards and are ready fortransition to secondary schools.
By 2016, national and community systems to support all girls and boys 0-6 years old in the targeted communities with a qualitystart to life, early learning and developmental readiness.

Key state-operated MDAs produce age/gender/location disaggregated reports by category on child abuse, children in conflict withthe law, child victims of major selected crimes and children seen in accident and emergency units.
By 2016, reproductive health, HIV/STI and mental health services meet standards for quality and adolescent friendliness.

Child protection services, for children in contact and conflict with the law, are in compliance with the CRC and otherinternational standards and deliver quality rehabilitation and re-integration services.
By 2016, inputs from adolescents and young people are utilized in governance mechanisms at regional and parish levels.
By 2016, interventions among adolescents including the most at risk are evidence-informed and supported by quality monitoring andevaluation frameworks.
Effective psychosocial services and community-based interventions are available for child victims of abuse, exploitation andviolence and children affected by emergencies
By 2016, quality data on ECD and education are made accessible in a timely manner to decision makers for their use to informnational policies, programmes, and advocacy efforts.
